The paper deals with the problem of encrypting individual sequences with perfect secrecy, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the concept of compressibility, which is related to data compression (cs.CR). The use of finite-state machines in the encryption process suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of redundancy, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses lossy reconstruction and side information, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
